The '''Grand Hallowed Coffin''' can be found at the end of the fifth floor in the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]]. It requires {{SCP|Thieving|66|link=yes}} {{Boostable|yes}} to open and grants 200 experience when successfully looted. Reaching the coffin requires {{SCP|Agility|92|link=yes}} {{Boostable|no}}. The player has unlimited time to loot the coffin (if it was reached within the time limit) once they jump over the pedestal, as the timer will pause by then. Occasionally when failing to loot the coffin, the player will be [[poison]]ed.

The [[strange old lockpick]] has an increased success chance at opening a coffin when compared to the standard [[lockpick]]. It will not use any charges to do this{{CiteReddit|author=Mod Husky|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/2007scape/comments/gzrpvi/problems_with_the_hallowed_sepulchre/fthzut1|title=Darkmeyer Improvements|quote=did you know that the strange old lockpick already has a higher success rate than a normal one, you can still fail but it's a bit lower|date=9 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/BFTpp|archivedate=13 June 2020}}.

Upon opening the Grand Hallowed Coffin, there is a 1% chance that the [[Archpriest of the Unicorn]] will appear. After speaking to him (with or without an [[amulet of ghostspeak]]), he will appear in the Hallowed Sepulchre's lobby if players wear a [[ring of visibility]].

